                    },
                    {
                        "name": "Breath Weapon",
                        "type": "offensive_action",
                        "text": "The bronze dragon breathes in one of two ways. The dragon can\u2019t use Breath Weapon again for 1d4 rounds.<ul><li><b>Lightning</b> (<a aonid=\"11\" game-obj=\"Traits\">arcane</a>, <a aonid=\"56\" game-obj=\"Traits\">electricity</a>, <a aonid=\"65\" game-obj=\"Traits\">evocation</a>); The dragon breathes lightning in a 80-foot line that deals 8d12 electricity damage (DC 33 basic Reflex save).</li><li><b>Repulsion Gas</b> (<a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Traits\">abjuration</a>, <a aonid=\"11\" game-obj=\"Traits\">arcane</a>, <a aonid=\"93\" game-obj=\"Traits\">incapacitation</a>, <a aonid=\"106\" game-obj=\"Traits\">mental</a>); The dragon breathes a 80-foot line of repulsive gas. Each creature in the area must succeed at a DC 33 Will save or become <a aonid=\"17\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">fleeing</a> from the dragon for 1 round (or 2 rounds on a critical failure).</li></ul>",
                        "action": {
                            "type": "stat_block_section",
                            "subtype": "action",
                            "name": "Two Actions",
                            "image": "TwoActions.png"
                        }
                    },
